The paper focuses on detecting fake news on social networks, which involves analyzing the patterns of news propagation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Additionally, the paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for analyzing news content, which could place it in the Computation and Language (cs.CL) category. The paper also deals with cybersecurity issues, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) category. The paper also involves analyzing the relationships among spreaders of fake news, which could place it in the Social and Cultural Anthropology (cs.SOC) category. Finally, the paper deals with detecting fake news, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
